                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true Ethiopian">
                              <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards covered with dark brown blind-tooled <material
                                key="leather">leather</material>. The inner sides of both boards are decorated with <material key="textile">textile</material> <term key="textileInlay">inlays</term>
                                featuring a floral motif outlined in yellow, white and green on a blue background.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                The boards are flush with the bookblock and present external shallow bevels.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Cover" color="dark brown">
                                Full dark-brown leather cover.
                                The turn-ins have been trimmed out and at the corners they form butt mitres.
                                <term key="additionalLeatherPatch">Additional leather patches</term> fill the gap between the turn-ins.
                                The cover shows a blind-tooled decoration, identical on both sides of the cover. The turn-ins and the edges are decorated as well.
                                The decoration consists of five concentric frames surrounding a central rectangular panel featuring a Latin cross.
                                Frames composed by the repetition of single tools, enclosed between <term key="tripleStraightLine">triple straight lines</term>,
                                alternate with empty ones.
                                Proceeding from the outer to the inner frame, the repeating decoration motifs are <term key="crissCross">criss-crosses</term>,
                                <term key="wavyLine">wavy lines</term>, and <term key="straightStrapwork">straight strapwork</term> elements.
                                The cross is formed by <term key="XForm">X-form</term> motifs between <term key="tripleStraightLine">triple straight lines</term>.
                                At the ends of the arms of the cross there are <term key="corniForm">corniform</term> motifs and six <term key="doubleCircle">double circles</term>.
                                Triple straight lines outline the shape of the cross, dividing the surrounding area in four panels in which are stamped four <term key="doubleCircle">double circles</term>
                                <term key="doubleCircle">Double circles</term> are stamped at the intersections of the straight lines and at the corners of the empty frames as well.
                                A <term key="singleStraightLine">single straight line</term> runs along the edges of the boards.
                                Turn-ins are decorated with concentric frames formed by <term key="tripleStraightLine">triple straight lines</term>.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Sewing">
                                Chainstitch sewing on four sewing stations (two pairs); periodic fold pattern; Z-plied threads.
                                Between each pair of sewing stations there are two lengths of thread.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>

                            </binding>
